prompts = ["Rectal prolapse is a condition in which part of the wall or the entire wall of the rectum falls out of place. Rectal prolapse can be a medical emergency. In some cases, the rectum may protrude.",
           "A coffee enema can cause numerous maladies including infections, sepsis (including campylobacter sepsis), severe electrolyte imbalance, colitis, polymicrobial enteric sepsis, proctocolitis, salmonella, brain abscess, and heart failure, and deaths related to coffee enemas have been documented.",
           "The word diarrhea is from the Ancient Greek from 'through' and 'flow'. Diarrhea is the spelling in American English, whereas diarrhoea is the spelling in British English. Slang terms for the condition include 'the runs', 'the squirts' (or 'squits' in Britain) and 'the trots'."]